<TITLE> BB rolls out July-December monetary policy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jul 19 (bdnews24.com)The central bank has announced a "pro-active accommodative" monetary policy for July-December with a provision to supply fund from its surplus foreign reserves to boost investment. "We want to identify this monetary policy as pro-active accommodative one, through which we want to earn desired GDP growth by boosting production and creating new jobs," Bangladesh Bank governor Atiur Rahman said as he announced the new policy in the capital on Sunday. "The main goal of this monetary policy is to assist a sustainable and productive growth by keeping inflation at a tolerable level." The new monetary policy's goals also include ensuring more credit flow to potential and productive sectors including agriculture and small and medium entrerprises and further developing the growth both in terms of quantity and quality, Rahman said. The central bank announces monetary policy twice a year. bdn
